The test_files module
=====================

	>>> print test.path.name
	test_files.test

	>>> import test_files

The module provides a method which gets all possible test files
	which means *.tests, *.test, *.py, in that order

We expect to find such extensions for this file here
	>>> scripts_here = test_files.get_test_scripts()
	>>> this_files_here = [ ts.basename() for ts in scripts_here if 'test_files' in ts]
	>>> show( this_files_here )
	['test_files.tests', 'test_files.test', 'test_files.py']

The method can also take arguments to search directories recursively
	and args is a list of possible stems 
	>>> stems = [ 'test_files', 'try' ]
	>>> show( [ ts.basename() for ts in test_files.get_test_scripts(recursive=False,args=stems) ])
	['test_files.tests', 'test_files.test', 'try.test', 'test_files.py', 'try.py']
